==English==

====Etymology====
Old English ''[[crēopan]]''

===Pronunciation===
* {{AHD|/krēp/}}, {{IPA|/kriːp/}}, {{SAMPA|/kri:p/}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-iːp|-iːp]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The movement of something that creeps.
# A gradual change in anything.
# {{cattag|publishing}} In sewn books, the tendancy of [[page]]s on the inside of a [[quire]] to stand out farther than those on the outside of it.
# {{cattag|materials science}} An increase in [[strain]] with time; the gradual [[flow]] or [[deformation]] of a material under [[stress]].
# {{geology}} the [[imperceptible]] [[downslope]] movement of surface [[rock]]
# {{cattag|informal|pejorative}} An annoyingly [[unpleasant]] person.
#: ''Stop following me, you '''creep'''!''

